## Phase 4: Spatial Solver (Placement)

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: READ POSITIONS FROM IMAGE FIRST!
**Before placing ANY object, look at the reference image and determine:**
1. Which quadrant/region is the object in? (top-left, bottom-center, etc.)
2. What is its approximate x_norm (0.0=left, 1.0=right)?
3. What is its approximate y_norm (0.0=top, 1.0=bottom)?

**Image Coordinate Mapping:**
```
Image Position → Blender World Coordinates
─────────────────────────────────────────
Top-Left     (x_norm≈0.2, y_norm≈0.2)  → x=-0.3*W, y=+0.3*D  (Northwest)
Top-Right    (x_norm≈0.8, y_norm≈0.2)  → x=+0.3*W, y=+0.3*D  (Northeast)
Bottom-Left  (x_norm≈0.2, y_norm≈0.8)  → x=-0.3*W, y=-0.3*D  (Southwest)
Bottom-Right (x_norm≈0.8, y_norm≈0.8)  → x=+0.3*W, y=-0.3*D  (Southeast)
Center       (x_norm≈0.5, y_norm≈0.5)  → x=0, y=0            (Center)
```

**⚠️ NOTE:** When calculating x_norm/y_norm, ignore any decorative borders in the image!
- Measure positions relative to the **actual room walls**, not image edges
- If the image has a border, treat the inner wall boundaries as 0.0 to 1.0 range

